<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>Making Closable</h2>
        <p>Pair the callout with the <Code>CloseButton</Code> attribute and <Code>ClosableData</Code> attribute to create a dismissable alert box.</p>
        <p>You can use the <Code>ClosableButtonCallBack</Code> attribute to add an event callback.</p>

        <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Containers.Callout TypeClass="primary">
            Any element can be used as a close trigger, not just close button. Adding the attribute <Code>CloseButton="true"</Code> to any element within the callout will turn it into a close trigger.

            When using the <Code>ClosableData</Code> attribute, you can optionally add <a href="https://get.foundation/sites/docs/motion-ui.html">Motion UI</a> classes to the attribute to change the closing animation. If no class is added, <Code>fade-out</Code> will be used by default.
        </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Containers.Callout>
        <HighlightCS Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90" HeaderTitle="Razor"
                     Content="" />

        <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Containers.Callout CloseButton="true" TypeClass="alert" ClosableData="">
            <h5>This is Important!</h5>
            <p>But when you're done reading it, click the close button in the corner to dismiss this alert.</p>
            <p>I'm using the default <Code>ClosableData</Code> parameters, and simply fade out.</p>
        </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Containers.Callout>

        <OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Containers.Callout CloseButton="true" TypeClass="success" ClosableData="slide-out-right">
            <h5>This a friendly message.</h5>
            <p>And when you're done with me, I can be closed using a Motion UI animation.</p>
        </OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Containers.Callout>


    </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>

